<p>In the latest development, Sudan’s paramilitary Rapid Support Forces (RSF) captured El Fasher in North Darfur and reports say fighters killed scores of civilians inside the city’s only partially functioning maternity hospital; the World Health Organization and Sudan Doctors Network said more than 460 people were killed and condemned the incident . Thousands of residents fled El Fasher after the takeover, and international bodies including the UN have called for an end to sieges and renewed diplomatic talks to halt further violence . Eyewitnesses and health workers described targeted attacks inside medical facilities and other civilian sites, heightening fears of mass atrocities in Darfur .</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/G0NZXlfrPmihM8C0xO7XYVn7LxdykMjzNFYM8JESoKjB1XeA2xobN-t2PUNOqm3u4c6yTGJ1SRbzoyeufVBvuzw2rleS7DME7K128y2AArVML2iH4vh5bSM4-KcoVQ8RYMMFztpa_N4QYIf3lL_dw4uI07cPlS6Ki-NDFkaNZ4gGuGZDxmWbxexHYERX0N_mUQn5KP0wg6FPNg' alt='A satellite image showing the Al Saudi Hospital in El Fasher, Sudan, on Tuesday.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Hospital&#x27;s role: The Saudi maternity hospital had been the last refuge for many starving or injured civilians in El Fasher before the attack, serving those displaced by earlier fighting .</li><li>Attacks beyond hospital: Reports and residents say killings also occurred at the university, the Interior Ministry building and elsewhere in the city, suggesting violence was widespread across civilian sites .</li><li>Diplomatic pressure: World leaders and international organizations called for renewed talks and urgent diplomacy to stop the fighting and secure humanitarian access after the city’s capture .</li><li>Criticism of responses: Human-rights advocates and commentators criticized some governments&#x27; muted statements and urged stronger action, with commentators linking foreign arms flows to escalating brutality .</li></ul><blockquote>They killed six wounded soldiers and civilians in their beds – some of them women. - Nawal Khalil</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>World Health Organization (WHO): The WHO said it was &quot;appalled and deeply shocked&quot; by reports that more than 460 people were killed at the Saudi maternity hospital and condemned the killings . (<a href='https://www.theguardian.com/world/2025/oct/29/hundreds-reportedly-killed-at-sudanese-hospital-as-evidence-of-rsf-atrocities-mounts'>The Guardian</a>)</li><li>Rapid Support Forces (RSF): The RSF has said it claimed control of El Fasher after taking the city on Sunday, according to multiple reports describing the group&#x27;s advance . (<a href='https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2025/oct/30/they-killed-civilians-in-their-beds-chaos-and-brutality-reign-after-fall-of-el-fasher'>The Guardian</a>)</li><li>Sudan Deputy Commissioner for Humanitarian Aid: Officials warn that tens of thousands fled the city amid reports of executions and rising civilian displacement in North Darfur . (<a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/africa/article/3330826/sudan-war-sparks-global-alarm-after-hundreds-reportedly-killed-hospital'>South China Morning Post</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2025/oct/30/they-killed-civilians-in-their-beds-chaos-and-brutality-reign-after-fall-of-el-fasher'>‘They killed civilians in their beds’: chaos and brutality reign after fall of El Fasher</a> - theguardian.com</li><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/africa/article/3330826/sudan-war-sparks-global-alarm-after-hundreds-reportedly-killed-hospital'>Sudan war sparks global alarm after hundreds killed at hospital</a> - scmp.com</li><li><a href='https://allafrica.com/stories/202510290632.html'>Sudan: El Fasher Hospital Patients &#x27;Collectively Eliminated&#x27; As Thousands Flee North Darfur Capital</a> - allafrica.com</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/sudan-with-hundreds-feared-dead-who-condemns-rsfs-massacre-at-el-fashers-only-hospital-13